<p>Performers: David Harrington (violin), John Sherba (violin),
Hank Dutt (viola), Joan Jeanrenaud (cello), Marja Mutru (harmonium),
David Lamb (bagpipe), Wu Man (zhong ruan, da ruan), Olov Johansson
(nyckelharpa), Huun-Huur Tu (vocals, igil, byzaanchi, toschpuluur)</p>

<p>Playing time: 68'</p>

<p>Recording dates: 1993-1997 (California &amp; New York)</p>

<p>For those readers unfamiliar with the Kronos Quartet, they are
very well-known in modern &amp; avant-garde music circles.  They
also have a certain predilection for &quot;New Age&quot;-type music,
and their entry into Early Music will be seen as an <em>event</em>
by some.  The present recital includes some other performers on
some tracks, and is unfortunately given with no notes on the music
other than specifying what it is, but is primarily string performance.
The famous EM pieces are handled with flair, but easily recognizable,
and the modern and/or world music pieces are generally in a similar
idiom.</p>

